ISLAMABAD, Feb 13 (APP):Prime Minister Imran Khan on Thursday chaired a meeting to review progress of the ongoing federal development schemes and projects in Sindh.
The meeting was attended by Minister for Planning Asad Umar, Minister for Information Technology Khalid Maqbool Siddiqui and relevant federal secretaries, a press release issued by the PM Media Office said.
